metadata.name: Number23-02
metadata.description: Micheal Jordan  Jordan led the Bulls to six NBA championships from 1991-98.  1991 NBA Finals  Chicago beat the Los Angeles Lakers led by Magic Johnson in five games.  1992 NBA Finals   Chicago beat Portland in six games for its second NBA championship. Jordan scored 35 of his 39 points. 1993 NBA Finals   Phoenix had NBA MVP Charles Barkley, but the Bulls won the series in six games behind Jordan, who averaged 41 points. 1996 NBA Finals   They beat Seattle in six games for their fourth NBA championship.  1997 NBA Finals   The Jazz had NBA MVP Karl Malone, but the Bulls won the series in six games behind Jordan, who averaged 32.3 points. 1998 NBA Finals   Chicago beat Utah in six games, and Jordan closed the series in Game 6 with "The Shot" over Byron Russell. Jordan averaged 33.5 points, four rebounds, and 2.3 assists in the series.
